{"TopicId":209158,"ForumId":112,"TopicTitle":"clamshell fairing deployment and parts blackening on reentry","CreatedByName":"darthvader15001","CreatedById":222173,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-30T19:47:13Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"darthvader15001","CreatedById":222173,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-30T19:47:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nso could you add clamshell deployment instead of that confetti deployment? it would also be nice to have\u00A0blacken on reentry.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nif anyone from intercept games sees this please put it into ksp2.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"t_v","CreatedById":213541,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-30T20:00:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224159591\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221659210433\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022222173\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022darthvader15001\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, darthvader15001 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nso could you add clamshell deployment instead of that confetti deployment? it would also be nice to have\u00A0blacken on reentry.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nif anyone from intercept games sees this please put it into ksp2.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust FYI, clamshell deployment exists for KSP 1. Right click on the fairing to open the menu, you can switch between clamshell and confetti, and you can also do interstage nodes!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI do hope that the feature continues in KSP 2., and maybe becomes the default.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Starwaster","CreatedById":71262,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-30T21:46:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/222173-darthvader15001/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022222173\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/222173-darthvader15001/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@darthvader15001\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/213541-t_v/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022213541\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/213541-t_v/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@t_v\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can also do it as a patch if you have Module Manager installed:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nclamshell.cfg\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E@PART[*]:HAS[@MODULE[ModuleProceduralFairing]]\n{\n\t@MODULE[ModuleProceduralFairing]\n\t{\n\t\t%useClamshell = True\n\t}\n}\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"t_v","CreatedById":213541,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-30T22:18:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks! I didn\u2019t think to patch it in. Maybe I should start doing patches more when I want to change something\u2026\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"darthgently","CreatedById":204885,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-31T16:05:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224159624\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221659217603\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002271262\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Starwaster\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 hours ago, Starwaster said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint\u0022\u003E%useClamshell\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cs\u003EWhat would be the setting names for the number of sides and the variant? It would be nice to default these to the values I typically use. I couldn\u0027t find the relevant info in any cfg files I looked in\u003C/s\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNevermind, found them in craft file!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-07-31T16:09:36Z\u0022 title=\u002207/31/2022 04:09  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 31, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by darthgently\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Starwaster","CreatedById":71262,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-08-01T07:15:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224159631\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221659219519\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022213541\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022t_v\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/30/2022 at 6:18 PM, t_v said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks! I didn\u2019t think to patch it in. Maybe I should start doing patches more when I want to change something\u2026\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have a folder for all my tweak patches that I\u0027ve been using for .... ten years? ish? It\u0027s the first thing that goes into GameData on a new modded install when updating KSP.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}